text: this class really builds upon what
people may know from one or two years
hands-on experience with AWS when you're
using AWS from day to day you're
learning what you need to use whereas
this course goes to a deeper dive on
some technologies and fills in what you
may not have learnt in your day to day
experience we do some advanced
networking topics on VPC we also talked
about some storage services like storage
gateway and deployment scenario is using
technology like Beanstalk I like the aha
moments in training like there will be
times when I'll explain something and
I'll just see the someone's face change
to Express I finally understand what
this service does and what I would use
it for there's been plenty of times in
class where someone's come to me with
something they're about to put into
production and we've white boarded it
talked through it and then design
something that did eventually go out
into production
